      "page": 2,
      "title": "Discover Your Free Phones",
      "article": "<div class=\"article\">\n<h1>Discover Your Free Phones</h1>\n<div class=\"ads ads-detail-one\" id=\"ads1\">\n<div class=\"advertisement\">Advertisement</div>\n<script async=\"\" crossorigin=\"anonymous\" src=\"https://pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js?client=ca-pub-2972155632292532\"></script>\n<!-- Phone Ads 1 -->\n<ins class=\"adsbygoogle\" data-ad-client=\"ca-pub-2972155632292532\" data-ad-format=\"auto\" data-ad-slot=\"2576564749\" data-full-width-responsive=\"true\" style=\"display:block\"></ins>\n<script>\n     (adsbygoogle = window.adsbygoogle || []).push({});\n</script>\n</div>\n<h4>1. Availability Of Free Cell Phone Programs</h4>\n<p>Actually, there are many free cell phone programs in the U.S., such as the Lifeline program and the Affordable Connectivity Program (ACP). ACP usually offers discount Internet services and devices to low-income individuals. And the federal program – Lifeline – provides free or low-cost phones and phone service to people in need.</p>\n<img alt=\"Discover Your Free Phones_2\" class=\"old_img\" data-smallsrc=\"//cdn.uslowcosthousing.com/Images/content_small/discover-your-free-phones/discover-your-free-phones_2.jpg\" data-src=\"//cdn.uslowcosthousing.com/Images/content/discover-your-free-phones/discover-your-free-phones_2.jpg\" data-webpsmallsrc=\"//cdn.uslowcosthousing.com/Images/content_small/discover-your-free-phones/discover-your-free-phones_2.webp\" data-webpsrc=\"//cdn.uslowcosthousing.com/Images/content/discover-your-free-phones/discover-your-free-phones_2.webp\" lazyload=\"\" src=\"/Public/Images/load.png\">\n</img></div>"
